article.description: Trevis Wyche scored 19 points and Quadir Welton and Antwon Portley each scored 11 and Saint Peter's controlled Niagara from the outset with a 66-53 win on Friday.
article.headline: Wyche leads St. Peter's attack in 66-53 win over Niagara
article.linkText: Wyche leads St. Peter's attack in 66-53 win over Niagara
article.story: LEWISTON, N.Y. -- Trevis Wyche scored 19 points and Quadir Welton and Antwon Portley each scored 11 and Saint Peter's controlled Niagara from the outset with a 66-53 win on Friday. Saint Peter's (17-12, 13-6 Metro Atlantic Athletic) raced to a 13-3 lead and never trailed. Wyche started the scoring with a layup, a 3-point play off a made layup, and another layup during the early run. Nick Griffin's 3-point play with four minutes before halftime made it a 30-15 lead and the Peacocks went to intermission with a 34-21 lead. Chris Barton buried a 3 to start a 7-0 run for Niagara (9-21, 6-13). Dominic Robb's layup brought the Purple Eagles to within 41-35 but they couldn't get closer. Welton added nine rebounds for the Peacocks, whose 13th conference win is a school record. Robb led the Purple Eagles with 15 points on 6-for-8 shooting and Kevin Larkin added 10.
